      • withInterval

        public LocationKitServiceOptions.Builder withInterval(java.lang.Long interval)
        Sets an interval in milliseconds for updates to be sent back to the app (either through the @{link ILocationEventListener}, a Pending Intent or a custom broadcast action. Note: recommended setting is null which will restul in LocationKit only sending events when it has updated location data. Use this setting only if you want to receive a location update every (n) interval regardless of if the device's location changed.
        Parameters:
        interval -
        Returns:
